{"name":"http-close","version":"0.0.2","description":"gracefully close open sockets in a http server","main":"index.js","dependencies":{"debug":"~0.7.2"},"devDependencies":{},"scripts":{},"repository":"https://github.com/tellnes/http-close","keywords":[],"license":"MIT","readme":"# http-close\n\nhttp-close keeps track on open sockets and closes them gracefully when the\ntcp server is closeing.\n\nIt does not handle\n\n## Usage\n\n```js\nvar http = require('http')\n  , httpClose = require('http-close')\n\nvar server = http.createServer()\n\n// Add http-close hook\nhttpClose({ timeout: 2000 }, server)\n\n// Just call server.close as usual when you want to stop the server\nserver.close()\n```\n\n## Install\n\n    $ npm install http-close\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n","versions":[{"number":"0.0.1","date":"2013-05-23T23:07:38.636Z"},{"number":"0.0.2","date":"2013-09-01T13:45:49.904Z"}],"created":"2013-05-23T23:07:31.283Z","modified":"2013-09-01T13:45:49.904Z","lastPublisher":{"name":"tellnes","email":"christian@tellnes.no"},"owners":[{"name":"tellnes","email":"christian@tellnes.no"}],"other":{"_attachments":{},"_from":".","_id":"http-close","_npmUser":{"name":"tellnes","email":"christian@tellnes.no"},"_npmVersion":"1.2.32","_rev":"1-a15d7f288cffd50e3e1a538a9728766d","author":{"name":"Christian Tellnes","email":"christian@tellnes.no","url":"http://christian.tellnes.com"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/tellnes/http-close/issues"},"directories":{},"dist-tags":{"latest":"0.0.2"},"dist":{"shasum":"165005cd294d69e10b4e7ee10421e3a40109ca18","tarball":"http://registry.npmjs.org/http-close/-/http-close-0.0.2.tgz"},"maintainers":[{"name":"tellnes","email":"christian@tellnes.no"}],"readmeFilename":"Readme.md","time":{"modified":"2013-09-01T13:45:49.904Z","created":"2013-05-23T23:07:31.283Z","0.0.1":"2013-05-23T23:07:38.636Z","0.0.2":"2013-09-01T13:45:49.904Z"}}}